    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nSee the example\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\n# distutils: extra_compile_args = -fopenmp\n# distutils: extra_link_args = -fopenmp\n\nfrom cython.parallel cimport prange\n\ncdef int _f():\n    for _ in prange(10, nogil=True):\n        return 5\n\ndef f():\n    return _f()\n```\n\nCalling `f()` returns `0`.\n\nTo me it doesn't look like `prange` is generating the relevant gotos in `switch(__pyx_parallel_why)`.\n\nIf you take a more complicated loop with an `else` block then it does work - this appears to be what we test.\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\n5\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.13\n\n### Cython version\n\nCurrent master (but I've gone back a bit and this looks like a long-standing bug)\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
